You are implementing the spec generation API routes (`app/api/pipeline/specs/run/route.ts` and supporting routes) for a video production pipeline editor. These endpoints trigger Claude Code to generate visual spec markdown files per section.

Requirements
1. `POST /api/pipeline/specs/run` — accepts `{ sections?: string[], files?: string[] }`. If sections omitted, generates all sections. Calls `runClaudeFix` with a spec generation prompt scoped to `specs/`. Returns SSE stream with `{ jobId }`.
2. `GET /api/pipeline/specs/list` — returns `{ sections: SpecSection[] }` where `SpecSection = { sectionId: string; files: SpecFile[] }` and `SpecFile = { path: string; visualType: 'remotion' | 'veo' | 'title' | 'split' | 'unknown'; status: 'exists' | 'missing' }`.
3. `GET /api/pipeline/specs/file?path=<relpath>` — reads and returns spec file content: `{ content: string }`. Returns 404 if not found.
4. `PUT /api/pipeline/specs/file` — accepts `{ path: string, content: string }`. Saves spec file with atomic write. Returns `{ ok: true }`.
5. No authentication required.
6. Visual type detection: parse the spec file first line for `[Remotion]`, `[veo:]`, `[title:]`, `[split:]` prefixes.

